ef="/wiki/Hessian_matrix" title="Hessian matrix">Hessian matrix</a></li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n</div>\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="padding:0 0.1em 0.4em">\n<div class="NavFrame collapsed" style="border:none;padding:0">\n<div class="NavHead" style="font-size:105%;background:transparent;text-align:left;text-align:center;"><span style="font-size:110%;">Specialized</span></div>\n<div class="NavContent" style="font-size:105%;padding:0.2em 0 0.4em;text-align:center;border-top:1px solid #aaa;padding-top:0.15em;border-bottom:1px solid #aaa;">\n<div class="hlist">\n<ul>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Fractional_calculus" title="Fractional calculus">Fractional</a></li>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Malliavin_calculus" title="Malliavin calculus">Malliavin</a></li>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Stochastic_calculus" title="Stochastic calculus">Stochastic</a></li>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Calculus_of_variations" title="Calculus of variations">Variations</a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align:right;font-size:115%;padding-top: 0.6em;">\n<div class="plainlinks hlist navbar mini">\n<ul>\n<li class="nv-view"><a href="/wiki/Template:Calculus" title="Template:Calculus"><abbr title="View this template">v</abbr></a></li>\n<li class="nv-talk"><a href="/wiki/Template_talk:Calculus" title="Template talk:Calculus"><abbr title="Discuss this template">t</abbr></a></li>\n<li class="nv-edit"><a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Template:Calculus&amp;action=edit"><abbr title="Edit this template">e</abbr></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n<p>In <a href="/wiki/Mathematics" title="Mathematics">mathematics</a>, <b>geometric calculus</b> extends the <a href="/wiki/Geometric_algebra" title="Geometric algebra">geometric algebra</a> to include <a href="/wiki/Derivative" title="Derivative">differentiation</a> and <a href="/wiki/Integral" title="Integral">integration</a>. The formalism is powerful and can be shown to encompass other mathematical theories including <a href="/wiki/Differential_geometry" title="Differential geometry">differential geometry</a> and <a href="/wiki/Differential_form" title="Differential form">differential forms</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-1">[1]</a></sup></p>\n<p></p>\n<div id="toc" class="toc">\n<div class="toctitle">\n<h2>Contents</h2>\n</div>\n<ul>\n<li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-1"><a href="#Differentiation"><span class="tocnumber">1</span> <span class="toctext">Differentiation</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class="toclevel-2 tocsection-2"><a href="#Product_rule"><span class="tocnumber">1.1</span> <span class="toctext">Product rule</span></a></li>\n<li class="toclevel-2 tocsection-3"><a href="#Interior_and_exterior_derivative"><span class="tocnumber">1.2</span> <span class="toctext">Interior and exterior derivative</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-4"><a href="#Integration"><span class="tocnumber">2</span> <span class="toctext">Integration</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class="toclevel-2 tocsection-5"><a href="#Fundamental_theorem_of_geometric_calculus"><span class="tocnumber">2.1</span> <span class="toctext">Fundamental theorem of geometric calculus</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-6"><a href="#Covariant_derivative"><span class="tocnumber">3</span> <span class="toctext">Covariant derivative</span></a></li>\n<li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-7"><a href="#Relation_to_differential_geometry"><span class="tocnumber">4</span> <span class="toctext">Relation to differential geometry</span></a></li>\n<li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-8"><a href="#Relation_to_differential_forms"><span class="tocnumber">5</span> <span class="toctext">Relation to differential forms</span></a></li>\n<li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-9"><a href="#History"><span class="tocnumber">6</span> <span class="toctext">History</span></a></li>\n<li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-10"><a href="#References_and_further_reading"><span class="tocnumber">7</span> <span class="toctext">References and further reading</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<p></p>\n<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Differentiation">Differentiation</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Geometric_calculus&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1" title="Edit section: Differentiation">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>With a geometric algebra given, let <i>a</i> and <i>b</i> be <a href="/wiki/Vector_(mathematics_and_physics)" title="Vector (mathematics and physics)">vectors</a> and let <i>F(a)</i> be a <a href="/wiki/Multivector" title="Multivector">multivector</a>-valued function. The <a href="/wiki/Directional_derivative" title="Directional derivative">directional derivative</a> of <i>F(a)</i> along <i>b</i> is defined as</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <msub>\n          <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2207;<!-- \xe2\x88\x87 --></mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>b</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>a</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <munder>\n          <mo movablelimits="true" form="prefix">lim</mo>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>&#x03F5;<!-- \xcf\xb5 --></mi>\n            <mo stretchy="false">&#x2192;<!-- \xe2\x86\x92 --></mo>\n            <mn>0</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </munder>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mfrac>\n            <mrow>\n              <mi>F</mi>\n              <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n              <mi>a</mi>\n              <mo>+</mo>\n              <mi>&#x03F5;<!-- \xcf\xb5 --></mi>\n              <mi>b</mi>\n              <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n              <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n              <mi>F</mi>\n              <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n              <mi>a</mi>\n              <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n            </mrow>\n            <mi>&#x03F5;<!-- \xcf\xb5 --></mi>\n          </mfrac>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle \\nabla _{b}F(a)=\\lim _{\\epsilon \\rightarrow 0}{\\frac {F(a+\\epsilon b)-F(a)}{\\epsilon }}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/64e09fa6601fe9cf31d70fd79788d98b9c21c458" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -2.005ex; width:32.614ex; height:5.843ex;" alt="\\nabla _{b}F(a)=\\lim _{{\\epsilon \\rightarrow 0}}{{\\frac  {F(a+\\epsilon b)-F(a)}{\\epsilon }}}" /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>provided that the limit exists, where the limit is taken for scalar <i>\xce\xb5</i>. This is similar to the usual definition of a directional derivative but extends it to functions that are not necessarily scalar-valued.</p>\n<p>Next, choose a set of <a href="/wiki/Basis_vector" class="mw-redirect" title="Basis vector">basis vectors</a> <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mo fence="false" stretchy="false">{</mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>i</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo fence="false" stretchy="false">}</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle \\{e_{i}\\}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/d45dea23899c892d30b142d73ed0fa19233ee4a5" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:4.247ex; height:2.843ex;" alt="\\{e_{i}\\}" /></span> and consider the operators, noted <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2202;<!-- \xe2\x88\x82 --></mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>i</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle (\\partial _{i})}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/b2735255e02ba74a1fd8ae5c5ee23cb8635dcf78" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:3.882ex; height:2.843ex;" alt="(\\partial _{i})" /></span>, that perform directional derivatives in the directions of <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>i</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle (e_{i})}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/056380dd5cc97207d5798e36224e0a4ba7103f5e" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:3.731ex; height:2.843ex;" alt="(e_{i})" /></span>:</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <msub>\n          <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2202;<!-- \xe2\x88\x82 --></mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>i</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo>:</mo>\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">&#x21A6;<!-- \xe2\x86\xa6 --></mo>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>x</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">&#x21A6;<!-- \xe2\x86\xa6 --></mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2207;<!-- \xe2\x88\x87 --></mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <msub>\n              <mi>e</mi>\n              <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                <mi>i</mi>\n              </mrow>\n            </msub>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>x</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle \\partial _{i}:F\\mapsto (x\\mapsto \\nabla _{e_{i}}F(x))}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/4722dbf3e51c6cd4b8477209ed0f08ea9406e174" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -1.005ex; width:24.675ex; height:3.009ex;" alt="\\partial _{i}:F\\mapsto (x\\mapsto \\nabla _{{e_{i}}}F(x))" /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>Then, using the <a href="/wiki/Einstein_summation_notation" class="mw-redirect" title="Einstein summation notation">Einstein summation notation</a>, consider the operator&#160;:</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <msup>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>i</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <msub>\n          <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2202;<!-- \xe2\x88\x82 --></mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>i</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle e^{i}\\partial _{i}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/16baf4cff5981ec5693572bed91cbdf4328133c3" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:3.953ex; height:3.009ex;" alt="e^{i}\\partial _{i}" /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>which means:</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">&#x21A6;<!-- \xe2\x86\xa6 --></mo>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>i</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <msub>\n          <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2202;<!-- \xe2\x88\x82 --></mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>i</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mi>F</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle F\\mapsto e^{i}\\partial _{i}F}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/67c5d46ffca526e24f079159fcd7fea6882e3abc" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:11.08ex; height:3.009ex;" alt="F\\mapsto e^{i}\\partial _{i}F" /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>or, more verbosely:</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">&#x21A6;<!-- \xe2\x86\xa6 --></mo>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>x</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">&#x21A6;<!-- \xe2\x86\xa6 --></mo>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>i</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <msub>\n          <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2207;<!-- \xe2\x88\x87 --></mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <msub>\n              <mi>e</mi>\n              <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                <mi>i</mi>\n              </mrow>\n            </msub>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>x</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle F\\mapsto (x\\mapsto e^{i}\\nabla _{e_{i}}F(x))}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/43b213074040f79685844384bca29a330ad3dd07" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -1.005ex; width:22.576ex; height:3.343ex;" alt="F\\mapsto (x\\mapsto e^{i}\\nabla _{{e_{i}}}F(x))" /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>It can be shown that this operator is independent of the choice of frame, and can thus be used to define the <i>geometric derivative</i>:</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2207;<!-- \xe2\x88\x87 --></mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>i</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <msub>\n          <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2202;<!-- \xe2\x88\x82 --></mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>i</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle \\nabla =e^{i}\\partial _{i}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/bc41205b7c3c3438bb99ed5d2832c0451393437e" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:9.008ex; height:3.009ex;" alt="\\nabla =e^{i}\\partial _{i}" /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>This is similar to the usual definition of the <a href="/wiki/Gradient" title="Gradient">gradient</a>, but it, too, extends to functions that are not necessarily scalar-valued.</p>\n<p>It can be shown that the directional derivative is linear regarding its direction, that is:</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <msub>\n          <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2207;<!-- \xe2\x88\x87 --></mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>&#x03B1;<!-- \xce\xb1 --></mi>\n            <mi>a</mi>\n            <mo>+</mo>\n            <mi>&#x03B2;<!-- \xce\xb2 --></mi>\n            <mi>b</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mi>&#x03B1;<!-- \xce\xb1 --></mi>\n        <msub>\n          <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2207;<!-- \xe2\x88\x87 --></mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>a</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo>+</mo>\n        <mi>&#x03B2;<!-- \xce\xb2 --></mi>\n        <msub>\n          <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2207;<!-- \xe2\x88\x87 --></mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>b</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle \\nabla _{\\alpha a+\\beta b}=\\alpha \\nabla _{a}+\\beta \\nabla _{b}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/08c9591374179c3c6855bfdf99384737c342768d" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -1.005ex; width:21.81ex; height:2.843ex;" alt="\\nabla _{{\\alpha a+\\beta b}}=\\alpha \\nabla _{a}+\\beta \\nabla _{b}" /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>From this follows that the directional derivative is the inner product of its direction by the geometric derivative. All needs to be observed is that the direction <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>a</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle a}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/ffd2487510aa438433a2579450ab2b3d557e5edc" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.24ex; height:1.676ex;" alt="a" /></span> can be written <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>a</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>a</mi>\n        <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x85 --></mo>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>i</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>i</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle a=(a\\cdot e^{i})e_{i}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/7bdd2a20374f16914502c8f46bbce43d8f3d037b" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:12.911ex; height:3.176ex;" alt="a=(a\\cdot e^{i})e_{i}" /></span>, so that:</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <msub>\n          <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2207;<!-- \xe2\x88\x87 --></mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>a</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2207;<!-- \xe2\x88\x87 --></mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n            <mi>a</mi>\n            <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x85 --></mo>\n            <msup>\n              <mi>e</mi>\n              <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                <mi>i</mi>\n              </mrow>\n            </msup>\n            <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n            <msub>\n              <mi>e</mi>\n              <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                <mi>i</mi>\n              </mrow>\n            </msub>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>a</mi>\n        <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x85 --></mo>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>i</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2207;<!-- \xe2\x88\x87 --></mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <msub>\n              <mi>e</mi>\n              <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                <mi>i</mi>\n              </mrow>\n            </msub>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mi>a</mi>\n        <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x85 --></mo>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>i</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <msub>\n          <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2207;<!-- \xe2\x88\x87 --></mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <msup>\n              <mi>e</mi>\n              <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                <mi>i</mi>\n              </mrow>\n            </msup>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mi>a</mi>\n        <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x85 --></mo>\n        <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2207;<!-- \xe2\x88\x87 --></mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle \\nabla _{a}=\\nabla _{(a\\cdot e^{i})e_{i}}=(a\\cdot e^{i})\\nabla _{e_{i}}=a\\cdot (e^{i}\\nabla _{e^{i}})=a\\cdot \\nabla }</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/5eb92f0ef4c7441fd0d3c035eaaf9635dc800748" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -1.171ex; width:48.479ex; height:3.509ex;" alt="\\nabla _{a}=\\nabla _{{(a\\cdot e^{i})e_{i}}}=(a\\cdot e^{i})\\nabla _{{e_{i}}}=a\\cdot (e^{i}\\nabla _{{e^{i}}})=a\\cdot \\nabla " /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>For this reason, <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <msub>\n          <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2207;<!-- \xe2\x88\x87 --></mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>a</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>x</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle \\nabla _{a}F(x)}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/778c451c134e3bc07df9aa0b3b55970b89efe7a7" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:7.977ex; height:2.843ex;" alt="\\nabla _{a}F(x)" /></span> is often noted <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>a</mi>\n        <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x85 --></mo>\n        <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2207;<!-- \xe2\x88\x87 --></mi>\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>x</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle a\\cdot \\nabla F(x)}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/38465ffedc81d50c3b85a6581e917858bd8b4f8a" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:9.798ex; height:2.843ex;" alt="a\\cdot \\nabla F(x)" /></span>.</p>\n<p>The standard <a href="/wiki/Order_of_operations" title="Order of operations">order of operations</a> for the geometric derivative is that it acts only on the function closest to its immediate right. Given two functions <i>F</i> and <i>G</i>, then for example we have</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2207;<!-- \xe2\x88\x87 --></mi>\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mi>G</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2207;<!-- \xe2\x88\x87 --></mi>\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mi>G</mi>\n        <mo>.</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle \\nabla FG=(\\nabla F)G.}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/2bb6a70cb331164b5877737eb40fa17690b398b5" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:16.666ex; height:2.843ex;" alt="\\nabla FG=(\\nabla F)G." /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Product_rule">Product rule</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Geometric_calculus&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2" title="Edit section: Product rule">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Although the partial derivative exhibits a <a href="/wiki/Product_rule" title="Product rule">product rule</a>, the geometric derivative only partially inherits this property. Consider two functions <i>F</i> and <i>G</i>:</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mtable columnalign="right left right left right left right left right left right left" rowspacing="3pt" columnspacing="0em 2em 0em 2em 0em 2em 0em 2em 0em 2em 0em" displaystyle="true">\n            <mtr>\n              <mtd>\n                <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2207;<!-- \xe2\x88\x87 --></mi>\n                <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n                <mi>F</mi>\n                <mi>G</mi>\n                <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n              </mtd>\n              <mtd>\n                <mi></mi>\n                <mo>=</mo>\n                <msup>\n                  <mi>e</mi>\n                  <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                    <mi>i</mi>\n                  </mrow>\n                </msup>\n                <msub>\n                  <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2202;<!-- \xe2\x88\x82 --></mi>\n                  <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                    <mi>i</mi>\n                  </mrow>\n                </msub>\n                <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n                <mi>F</mi>\n                <mi>G</mi>\n                <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n              </mtd>\n            </mtr>\n            <mtr>\n              <mtd />\n              <mtd>\n                <mi></mi>\n                <mo>=</mo>\n                <msup>\n                  <mi>e</mi>\n                  <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                    <mi>i</mi>\n                  </mrow>\n                </msup>\n                <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n                <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n                <msub>\n                  <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2202;<!-- \xe2\x88\x82 --></mi>\n                  <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                    <mi>i</mi>\n                  </mrow>\n                </msub>\n                <mi>F</mi>\n                <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n                <mi>G</mi>\n                <mo>+</mo>\n                <mi>F</mi>\n                <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n                <msub>\n                  <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2202;<!-- \xe2\x88\x82 --></mi>\n                  <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                    <mi>i</mi>\n                  </mrow>\n                </msub>\n                <mi>G</mi>\n                <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n                <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n              </mtd>\n            </mtr>\n            <mtr>\n              <mtd />\n              <mtd>\n                <mi></mi>\n                <mo>=</mo>\n                <msup>\n                  <mi>e</mi>\n                  <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                    <mi>i</mi>\n                  </mrow>\n                </msup>\n                <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n                <msub>\n                  <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2202;<!-- \xe2\x88\x82 --></mi>\n                  <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                    <mi>i</mi>\n                  </mrow>\n                </msub>\n                <mi>F</mi>\n                <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n                <mi>G</mi>\n                <mo>+</mo>\n                <msup>\n                  <mi>e</mi>\n                  <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                    <mi>i</mi>\n                  </mrow>\n                </msup>\n                <mi>F</mi>\n                <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n                <msub>\n                  <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2202;<!-- \xe2\x88\x82 --></mi>\n                  <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                    <mi>i</mi>\n                  </mrow>\n                </msub>\n                <mi>G</mi>\n                <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n              </mtd>\n            </mtr>\n          </mtable>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle {\\begin{aligned}\\nabla (FG)&amp;=e^{i}\\partial _{i}(FG)\\\\&amp;=e^{i}((\\partial _{i}F)G+F(\\partial _{i}G))\\\\&amp;=e^{i}(\\partial _{i}F)G+e^{i}F(\\partial _{i}G)\\end{aligned}}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/79355c3927833c46589129bc5293ef6a5c39fec2" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -4.338ex; width:32.819ex; height:9.843ex;" alt="{\\begin{aligned}\\nabla (FG)&amp;=e^{i}\\partial _{i}(FG)\\\\&amp;=e^{i}((\\partial _{i}F)G+F(\\partial _{i}G))\\\\&amp;=e^{i}(\\partial _{i}F)G+e^{i}F(\\partial _{i}G)\\end{aligned}}" /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>Since the geometric product is not <a href="/wiki/Commutative" class="mw-redirect" title="Commutative">commutative</a> with <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <msup>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>i</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mo>&#x2260;<!-- \xe2\x89\xa0 --></mo>\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>i</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle e^{i}F\\neq Fe^{i}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/3fd916db9bd3b5480356f17741403d1b3d8035fe" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:10.413ex; height:3.176ex;" alt="e^{i}F\\neq Fe^{i}" /></span> in general, we cannot proceed further without new notation. A solution is to adopt the <i><a href="/wiki/Overdot" class="mw-redirect" title="Overdot">overdot</a> notation</i>, in which the scope of a geometric derivative with an overdot is the multivector-valued function sharing the same overdot. In this case, if we define</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mover>\n              <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2207;<!-- \xe2\x88\x87 --></mi>\n              <mo>&#x02D9;<!-- \xcb\x99 --></mo>\n            </mover>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mover>\n              <mi>G</mi>\n              <mo>&#x02D9;<!-- \xcb\x99 --></mo>\n            </mover>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>i</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2202;<!-- \xe2\x88\x82 --></mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>i</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mi>G</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mo>,</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle {\\dot {\\nabla }}F{\\dot {G}}=e^{i}F(\\partial _{i}G),}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/f4ac4039824ab1c45fc76716911bbeb1cc6c15e6" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:18.673ex; height:3.343ex;" alt="{\\dot  {\\nabla }}F{\\dot  {G}}=e^{i}F(\\partial _{i}G)," /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>then the product rule for the geometric derivative is</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2207;<!-- \xe2\x88\x87 --></mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mi>G</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2207;<!-- \xe2\x88\x87 --></mi>\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mi>G</mi>\n        <mo>+</mo>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mover>\n              <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2207;<!-- \xe2\x88\x87 --></mi>\n              <mo>&#x02D9;<!-- \xcb\x99 --></mo>\n            </mover>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mover>\n              <mi>G</mi>\n              <mo>&#x02D9;<!-- \xcb\x99 --></mo>\n            </mover>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle \\nabla (FG)=\\nabla FG+{\\dot {\\nabla }}F{\\dot {G}}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/873b9669510386f563537f1ca3a4b88849e4822d" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:24.394ex; height:3.343ex;" alt="\\nabla (FG)=\\nabla FG+{\\dot  {\\nabla }}F{\\dot  {G}}" /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Interior_and_exterior_derivative">Interior and exterior derivative</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Geometric_calculus&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3" title="Edit section: Interior and exterior derivative">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Let <i>F</i> be an <i>r</i>-grade multivector. Then we can define an additional pair of operators, the interior and exterior derivatives,</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2207;<!-- \xe2\x88\x87 --></mi>\n        <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x85 --></mo>\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mo fence="false" stretchy="false">&#x27E8;<!-- \xe2\x9f\xa8 --></mo>\n        <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2207;<!-- \xe2\x88\x87 --></mi>\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <msub>\n          <mo fence="false" stretchy="false">&#x27E9;<!-- \xe2\x9f\xa9 --></mo>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>r</mi>\n            <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>i</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x85 --></mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2202;<!-- \xe2\x88\x82 --></mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>i</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mi>F</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle \\nabla \\cdot F=\\langle \\nabla F\\rangle _{r-1}=e^{i}\\cdot \\partial _{i}F}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/4982ceb08e2e5397c24425df283217bd4c4d54b1" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:27.623ex; height:3.176ex;" alt="\\nabla \\cdot F=\\langle \\nabla F\\rangle _{{r-1}}=e^{i}\\cdot \\partial _{i}F" /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2207;<!-- \xe2\x88\x87 --></mi>\n        <mo>&#x2227;<!-- \xe2\x88\xa7 --></mo>\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mo fence="false" stretchy="false">&#x27E8;<!-- \xe2\x9f\xa8 --></mo>\n        <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2207;<!-- \xe2\x88\x87 --></mi>\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <msub>\n          <mo fence="false" stretchy="false">&#x27E9;<!-- \xe2\x9f\xa9 --></mo>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>r</mi>\n            <mo>+</mo>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>i</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mo>&#x2227;<!-- \xe2\x88\xa7 --></mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2202;<!-- \xe2\x88\x82 --></mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>i</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mo>.</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle \\nabla \\wedge F=\\langle \\nabla F\\rangle _{r+1}=e^{i}\\wedge \\partial _{i}F.}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/c0321f3d2a4d42f07dcf7ba7732cecf9eae40693" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:30.087ex; height:3.176ex;" alt="\\nabla \\wedge F=\\langle \\nabla F\\rangle _{{r+1}}=e^{i}\\wedge \\partial _{i}F." /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>In particular, if <i>F</i> is grade 1 (vector-valued function), then we can write</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2207;<!-- \xe2\x88\x87 --></mi>\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2207;<!-- \xe2\x88\x87 --></mi>\n        <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x85 --></mo>\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mo>+</mo>\n        <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2207;<!-- \xe2\x88\x87 --></mi>\n        <mo>&#x2227;<!-- \xe2\x88\xa7 --></mo>\n        <mi>F</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle \\nabla F=\\nabla \\cdot F+\\nabla \\wedge F}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/82870582fd3129b3857583aa3fc23db8b061444e" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.505ex; width:21.335ex; height:2.343ex;" alt="\\nabla F=\\nabla \\cdot F+\\nabla \\wedge F" /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>and identify the <a href="/wiki/Divergence" title="Divergence">divergence</a> and <a href="/wiki/Curl_(mathematics)" title="Curl (mathematics)">curl</a> as</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2207;<!-- \xe2\x88\x87 --></mi>\n        <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x85 --></mo>\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mi>div</mi>\n        <mo>&#x2061;<!-- \xe2\x81\xa1 --></mo>\n        <mi>F</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle \\nabla \\cdot F=\\operatorname {div} F}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/83eaeb74ac92cd447f1eefa0bcc6680ecce10fc6" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:13.833ex; height:2.176ex;" alt="\\nabla \\cdot F=\\operatorname {div}F" /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2207;<!-- \xe2\x88\x87 --></mi>\n        <mo>&#x2227;<!-- \xe2\x88\xa7 --></mo>\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mi>I</mi>\n        <mspace width="thinmathspace" />\n        <mi>curl</mi>\n        <mo>&#x2061;<!-- \xe2\x81\xa1 --></mo>\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mo>.</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle \\nabla \\wedge F=I\\,\\operatorname {curl} F.}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/c3d12e72efa70a877990888074ff3e79afdc1dfd" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:18.077ex; height:2.176ex;" alt="\\nabla \\wedge F=I\\,\\operatorname {curl}F." /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>Note, however, that these two operators are considerably weaker than the geometric derivative counterpart for several reasons. Neither the interior derivative operator nor the exterior derivative operator is <a href="/wiki/Invertible" class="mw-redirect" title="Invertible">invertible</a>.</p>\n<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Integration">Integration</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Geometric_calculus&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4" title="Edit section: Integration">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Let <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mo fence="false" stretchy="false">{</mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo>,</mo>\n        <mspace width="thinmathspace" />\n        <mo>.</mo>\n        <mo>.</mo>\n        <mo>.</mo>\n        <mspace width="thinmathspace" />\n        <msub>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>n</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo fence="false" stretchy="false">}</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle \\{e_{1},\\,...\\,e_{n}\\}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/41912fead7e0c88d6df88535e3a5ef35081fed98" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:11.773ex; height:2.843ex;" alt="\\{e_{1},\\,...\\,e_{n}\\}" /></span> be a set of basis vectors that span an <i>n</i>-dimensional vector space. From geometric algebra, we interpret the <a href="/wiki/Pseudoscalar" title="Pseudoscalar">pseudoscalar</a> <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <msub>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo>&#x2227;<!-- \xe2\x88\xa7 --></mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo>&#x2227;<!-- \xe2\x88\xa7 --></mo>\n        <mo>&#x22EF;<!-- \xe2\x8b\xaf --></mo>\n        <mo>&#x2227;<!-- \xe2\x88\xa7 --></mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>n</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle e_{1}\\wedge e_{2}\\wedge \\cdots \\wedge e_{n}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/46c010c96b20bb36cc5ba75356c97b237eab2c3a" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:17.144ex; height:2.343ex;" alt="e_{1}\\wedge e_{2}\\wedge \\cdots \\wedge e_{n}" /></span> to be the <a href="/wiki/Signed_volume" class="mw-redirect" title="Signed volume">signed volume</a> of the <i>n</i>-<a href="/wiki/Parallelepiped#Parallelotope" title="Parallelepiped">parallelotope</a> subtended by these basis vectors. If the basis vectors are <a href="/wiki/Orthonormal" class="mw-redirect" title="Orthonormal">orthonormal</a>, then this is the unit pseudoscalar.</p>\n<p>More generally, we may restrict ourselves to a subset of <i>k</i> of the basis vectors, where <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mn>1</mn>\n        <mo>&#x2264;<!-- \xe2\x89\xa4 --></mo>\n        <mi>k</mi>\n        <mo>&#x2264;<!-- \xe2\x89\xa4 --></mo>\n        <mi>n</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle 1\\leq k\\leq n}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/78ec00bc2eb99b403bee93def3c12ae87f1e3c3d" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:10.018ex; height:2.509ex;" alt="1\\leq k\\leq n" /></span>, to treat the length, area, or other general <i>k</i>-volume of a subspace in the overall <i>n</i>-dimensional vector space. We denote these selected basis vectors by <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mo fence="false" stretchy="false">{</mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <msub>\n              <mi>i</mi>\n              <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                <mn>1</mn>\n              </mrow>\n            </msub>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo>,</mo>\n        <mspace width="thinmathspace" />\n        <mo>.</mo>\n        <mo>.</mo>\n        <mo>.</mo>\n        <mspace width="thinmathspace" />\n        <msub>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <msub>\n              <mi>i</mi>\n              <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                <mi>k</mi>\n              </mrow>\n            </msub>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo fence="false" stretchy="false">}</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle \\{e_{i_{1}},\\,...\\,e_{i_{k}}\\}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/fc61906ca229daad60f24f18efea2ba2dd6014fa" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -1.005ex; width:12.803ex; height:3.009ex;" alt="\\{e_{{i_{1}}},\\,...\\,e_{{i_{k}}}\\}" /></span>. A general <i>k</i>-volume of the <i>k</i>-parallelotope subtended by these basis vectors is the grade <i>k</i> multivector <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <msub>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <msub>\n              <mi>i</mi>\n              <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                <mn>1</mn>\n              </mrow>\n            </msub>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo>&#x2227;<!-- \xe2\x88\xa7 --></mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <msub>\n              <mi>i</mi>\n              <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                <mn>2</mn>\n              </mrow>\n            </msub>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo>&#x2227;<!-- \xe2\x88\xa7 --></mo>\n        <mo>&#x22EF;<!-- \xe2\x8b\xaf --></mo>\n        <mo>&#x2227;<!-- \xe2\x88\xa7 --></mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <msub>\n              <mi>i</mi>\n              <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                <mi>k</mi>\n              </mrow>\n            </msub>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle e_{i_{1}}\\wedge e_{i_{2}}\\wedge \\cdots \\wedge e_{i_{k}}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/510f51896e7d8e37d60291da9ee9e3b2cdabe5b9" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -1.005ex; width:18.757ex; height:2.676ex;" alt="e_{{i_{1}}}\\wedge e_{{i_{2}}}\\wedge \\cdots \\wedge e_{{i_{k}}}" /></span>.</p>\n<p>Even more generally, we may consider a new set of vectors <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mo fence="false" stretchy="false">{</mo>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>x</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <msub>\n              <mi>i</mi>\n              <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                <mn>1</mn>\n              </mrow>\n            </msub>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <msub>\n              <mi>i</mi>\n              <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                <mn>1</mn>\n              </mrow>\n            </msub>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo>,</mo>\n        <mspace width="thinmathspace" />\n        <mo>.</mo>\n        <mo>.</mo>\n        <mo>.</mo>\n        <mspace width="thinmathspace" />\n        <msup>\n          <mi>x</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <msub>\n              <mi>i</mi>\n              <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                <mi>k</mi>\n              </mrow>\n            </msub>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <msub>\n              <mi>i</mi>\n              <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                <mi>k</mi>\n              </mrow>\n            </msub>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo fence="false" stretchy="false">}</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle \\{x^{i_{1}}e_{i_{1}},\\,...\\,x^{i_{k}}e_{i_{k}}\\}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/399ed5a4aafcb7a57ea5ee783dd5038fe17043ce" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -1.005ex; width:18.8ex; height:3.343ex;" alt="\\{x^{{i_{1}}}e_{{i_{1}}},\\,...\\,x^{{i_{k}}}e_{{i_{k}}}\\}" /></span> proportional to the <i>k</i> basis vectors, where each of the <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mo fence="false" stretchy="false">{</mo>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>x</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <msub>\n              <mi>i</mi>\n              <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                <mi>j</mi>\n              </mrow>\n            </msub>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mo fence="false" stretchy="false">}</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle \\{x^{i_{j}}\\}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/a8a4327ee9dcd8e05486d777608ac8a121511a7c" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:5.213ex; height:3.176ex;" alt="\\{x^{{i_{j}}}\\}" /></span> is a component that scales one of the basis vectors. We are free to choose components as infinitesimally small as we wish as long as they remain nonzero. Since the outer product of these terms can be interpreted as a <i>k</i>-volume, a natural way to define a <a href="/wiki/Measure_(mathematics)" title="Measure (mathematics)">measure</a> is</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mtable columnalign="right left right left right left right left right left right left" rowspacing="3pt" columnspacing="0em 2em 0em 2em 0em 2em 0em 2em 0em 2em 0em" displaystyle="true">\n            <mtr>\n              <mtd>\n                <msup>\n                  <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                    <mi mathvariant="normal">d</mi>\n                  </mrow>\n                  <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                    <mi>k</mi>\n                  </mrow>\n                </msup>\n                <mi>X</mi>\n              </mtd>\n              <mtd>\n                <mi></mi>\n                <mo>=</mo>\n                <mrow>\n                  <mo>(</mo>\n                  <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                    <mi mathvariant="normal">d</mi>\n                  </mrow>\n                  <msup>\n                    <mi>x</mi>\n                    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                      <msub>\n                        <mi>i</mi>\n                        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                          <mn>1</mn>\n                        </mrow>\n                      </msub>\n                    </mrow>\n                  </msup>\n                  <msub>\n                    <mi>e</mi>\n                    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                      <msub>\n                        <mi>i</mi>\n                        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                          <mn>1</mn>\n                        </mrow>\n                      </msub>\n                    </mrow>\n                  </msub>\n                  <mo>)</mo>\n                </mrow>\n                <mo>&#x2227;<!-- \xe2\x88\xa7 --></mo>\n                <mrow>\n                  <mo>(</mo>\n                  <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                    <mi mathvariant="normal">d</mi>\n                  </mrow>\n                  <msup>\n                    <mi>x</mi>\n                    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                      <msub>\n                        <mi>i</mi>\n                        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                          <mn>2</mn>\n                        </mrow>\n                      </msub>\n                    </mrow>\n                  </msup>\n                  <msub>\n                    <mi>e</mi>\n                    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                      <msub>\n                        <mi>i</mi>\n                        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                          <mn>2</mn>\n                        </mrow>\n                      </msub>\n                    </mrow>\n                  </msub>\n                  <mo>)</mo>\n                </mrow>\n                <mo>&#x2227;<!-- \xe2\x88\xa7 --></mo>\n                <mo>&#x22EF;<!-- \xe2\x8b\xaf --></mo>\n                <mo>&#x2227;<!-- \xe2\x88\xa7 --></mo>\n                <mrow>\n                  <mo>(</mo>\n                  <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                    <mi mathvariant="normal">d</mi>\n                  </mrow>\n                  <msup>\n                    <mi>x</mi>\n                    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                      <msub>\n                        <mi>i</mi>\n                        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                          <mi>k</mi>\n                        </mrow>\n                      </msub>\n                    </mrow>\n                  </msup>\n                  <msub>\n                    <mi>e</mi>\n                    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                      <msub>\n                        <mi>i</mi>\n                        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                          <mi>k</mi>\n                        </mrow>\n                      </msub>\n                    </mrow>\n                  </msub>\n                  <mo>)</mo>\n                </mrow>\n              </mtd>\n            </mtr>\n            <mtr>\n              <mtd />\n              <mtd>\n                <mi></mi>\n                <mo>=</mo>\n                <mrow>\n                  <mo>(</mo>\n                  <msub>\n                    <mi>e</mi>\n                    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                      <msub>\n                        <mi>i</mi>\n                        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                          <mn>1</mn>\n                        </mrow>\n                      </msub>\n                    </mrow>\n                  </msub>\n                  <mo>&#x2227;<!-- \xe2\x88\xa7 --></mo>\n                  <msub>\n                    <mi>e</mi>\n                    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                      <msub>\n                        <mi>i</mi>\n                        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                          <mn>2</mn>\n                        </mrow>\n                      </msub>\n                    </mrow>\n                  </msub>\n                  <mo>&#x2227;<!-- \xe2\x88\xa7 --></mo>\n                  <mo>&#x22EF;<!-- \xe2\x8b\xaf --></mo>\n                  <mo>&#x2227;<!-- \xe2\x88\xa7 --></mo>\n                  <msub>\n                    <mi>e</mi>\n                    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                      <msub>\n                        <mi>i</mi>\n                        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                          <mi>k</mi>\n                        </mrow>\n                      </msub>\n                    </mrow>\n                  </msub>\n                  <mo>)</mo>\n                </mrow>\n                <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                  <mi mathvariant="normal">d</mi>\n                </mrow>\n                <msup>\n                  <mi>x</mi>\n                  <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                    <msub>\n                      <mi>i</mi>\n                      <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                        <mn>1</mn>\n                      </mrow>\n                    </msub>\n                  </mrow>\n                </msup>\n                <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                  <mi mathvariant="normal">d</mi>\n                </mrow>\n                <msup>\n                  <mi>x</mi>\n                  <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                    <msub>\n                      <mi>i</mi>\n                      <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                        <mn>2</mn>\n                      </mrow>\n                    </msub>\n                  </mrow>\n                </msup>\n                <mo>&#x22EF;<!-- \xe2\x8b\xaf --></mo>\n                <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                  <mi mathvariant="normal">d</mi>\n                </mrow>\n                <msup>\n                  <mi>x</mi>\n                  <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                    <msub>\n                      <mi>i</mi>\n                      <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                        <mi>k</mi>\n                      </mrow>\n                    </msub>\n                  </mrow>\n                </msup>\n              </mtd>\n            </mtr>\n          </mtable>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle {\\begin{aligned}\\mathrm {d} ^{k}X&amp;=\\left(\\mathrm {d} x^{i_{1}}e_{i_{1}}\\right)\\wedge \\left(\\mathrm {d} x^{i_{2}}e_{i_{2}}\\right)\\wedge \\cdots \\wedge \\left(\\mathrm {d} x^{i_{k}}e_{i_{k}}\\right)\\\\&amp;=\\left(e_{i_{1}}\\wedge e_{i_{2}}\\wedge \\cdots \\wedge e_{i_{k}}\\right)\\mathrm {d} x^{i_{1}}\\mathrm {d} x^{i_{2}}\\cdots \\mathrm {d} x^{i_{k}}\\end{aligned}}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/f81b39e02a782e1bd5585597c1d43546008bcea0" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -3.005ex; width:46.35ex; height:7.176ex;" alt="{\\begin{aligned}{\\mathrm  {d}}^{k}X&amp;=\\left({\\mathrm  {d}}x^{{i_{1}}}e_{{i_{1}}}\\right)\\wedge \\left({\\mathrm  {d}}x^{{i_{2}}}e_{{i_{2}}}\\right)\\wedge \\cdots \\wedge \\left({\\mathrm  {d}}x^{{i_{k}}}e_{{i_{k}}}\\right)\\\\&amp;=\\left(e_{{i_{1}}}\\wedge e_{{i_{2}}}\\wedge \\cdots \\wedge e_{{i_{k}}}\\right){\\mathrm  {d}}x^{{i_{1}}}{\\mathrm  {d}}x^{{i_{2}}}\\cdots {\\mathrm  {d}}x^{{i_{k}}}\\end{aligned}}" /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>The measure is therefore always proportional to the unit pseudoscalar of a <i>k</i>-dimensional subspace of the vector space. Compare the <a href="/wiki/Riemannian_volume_form" class="mw-redirect" title="Riemannian volume form">Riemannian volume form</a> in the theory of differential forms. The integral is taken with respect to this measure:</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <msub>\n          <mo>&#x222B;<!-- \xe2\x88\xab --></mo>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>V</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>x</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <msup>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi mathvariant="normal">d</mi>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>k</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mi>X</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mo>&#x222B;<!-- \xe2\x88\xab --></mo>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>V</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>x</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <mo>(</mo>\n          <msub>\n            <mi>e</mi>\n            <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n              <msub>\n                <mi>i</mi>\n                <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                  <mn>1</mn>\n                </mrow>\n              </msub>\n            </mrow>\n          </msub>\n          <mo>&#x2227;<!-- \xe2\x88\xa7 --></mo>\n          <msub>\n            <mi>e</mi>\n            <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n              <msub>\n                <mi>i</mi>\n                <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                  <mn>2</mn>\n                </mrow>\n              </msub>\n            </mrow>\n          </msub>\n          <mo>&#x2227;<!-- \xe2\x88\xa7 --></mo>\n          <mo>&#x22EF;<!-- \xe2\x8b\xaf --></mo>\n          <mo>&#x2227;<!-- \xe2\x88\xa7 --></mo>\n          <msub>\n            <mi>e</mi>\n            <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n              <msub>\n                <mi>i</mi>\n                <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                  <mi>k</mi>\n                </mrow>\n              </msub>\n            </mrow>\n          </msub>\n          <mo>)</mo>\n        </mrow>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mi mathvariant="normal">d</mi>\n        </mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>x</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <msub>\n              <mi>i</mi>\n              <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                <mn>1</mn>\n              </mrow>\n            </msub>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mi mathvariant="normal">d</mi>\n        </mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>x</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <msub>\n              <mi>i</mi>\n              <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                <mn>2</mn>\n              </mrow>\n            </msub>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mo>&#x22EF;<!-- \xe2\x8b\xaf --></mo>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mi mathvariant="normal">d</mi>\n        </mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>x</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <msub>\n              <mi>i</mi>\n              <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                <mi>k</mi>\n              </mrow>\n            </msub>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle \\int _{V}F(x)\\mathrm {d} ^{k}X=\\int _{V}F(x)\\left(e_{i_{1}}\\wedge e_{i_{2}}\\wedge \\cdots \\wedge e_{i_{k}}\\right)\\mathrm {d} x^{i_{1}}\\mathrm {d} x^{i_{2}}\\cdots \\mathrm {d} x^{i_{k}}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/37b1ca877aad9cb181a17eea20436325d67f2fff" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -2.338ex; width:61.809ex; height:5.843ex;" alt="\\int _{V}F(x){\\mathrm  {d}}^{k}X=\\int _{V}F(x)\\left(e_{{i_{1}}}\\wedge e_{{i_{2}}}\\wedge \\cdots \\wedge e_{{i_{k}}}\\right){\\mathrm  {d}}x^{{i_{1}}}{\\mathrm  {d}}x^{{i_{2}}}\\cdots {\\mathrm  {d}}x^{{i_{k}}}" /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>More formally, consider some directed volume <i>V</i> of the subspace. We may divide this volume into a sum of <a href="/wiki/Simplices" class="mw-redirect" title="Simplices">simplices</a>. Let <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mo fence="false" stretchy="false">{</mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>x</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>i</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo fence="false" stretchy="false">}</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle \\{x_{i}\\}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/c9d90fd628e1497151325d23b808b6d0296e7701" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:4.493ex; height:2.843ex;" alt="\\{x_i\\}" /></span> be the coordinates of the vertices. At each vertex we assign a measure <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x0394;<!-- \xce\x94 --></mi>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>U</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>i</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>x</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle \\Delta U_{i}(x)}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/0790285493fc7f88216392e6b60ea8cef387c1cd" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:7.522ex; height:2.843ex;" alt="\\Delta U_{i}(x)" /></span> as the average measure of the simplices sharing the vertex. Then the integral of <i>F(x)</i> with respect to <i>U(x)</i> over this volume is obtained in the limit of finer partitioning of the volume into smaller simplices:</p>\n<p><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <msub>\n          <mo>&#x222B;<!-- \xe2\x88\xab --></mo>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>V</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mi>d</mi>\n        <mi>U</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <munder>\n          <mo movablelimits="true" form="prefix">lim</mo>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>n</mi>\n            <mo stretchy="false">&#x2192;<!-- \xe2\x86\x92 --></mo>\n            <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x221E;<!-- \xe2\x88\x9e --></mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </munder>\n        <munderover>\n          <mo>&#x2211;<!-- \xe2\x88\x91 --></mo>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>i</mi>\n            <mo>=</mo>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>n</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </munderover>\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>x</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>i</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x0394;<!-- \xce\x94 --></mi>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>U</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>i</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>x</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mo>.</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle \\int _{V}FdU=\\lim _{n\\rightarrow \\infty }\\sum _{i=1}^{n}F(x_{i})\\Delta U_{i}(x).}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/814106473463332a61ef009b1e1f53f80c8bd848" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -3.005ex; width:33.415ex; height:7.009ex;" alt="\\int _{V}FdU=\\lim _{{n\\rightarrow \\infty }}\\sum _{{i=1}}^{n}F(x_{i})\\Delta U_{i}(x)." /></span></p>\n<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Fundamental_theorem_of_geometric_calculus">Fundamental theorem of geometric calculus</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Geometric_calculus&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5" title="Edit section: Fundamental theorem of geometric calculus">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>The reason for defining the geometric derivative and integral as above is that they allow a strong generalization of <a href="/wiki/Stokes%27_theorem" title="Stokes\' theorem">Stokes\' theorem</a>. Let <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi mathvariant="sans-serif">L</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>A</mi>\n        <mo>;</mo>\n        <mi>x</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle {\\mathsf {L}}(A;x)}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/f591f35b9bf0a4095d47b925aab09a9df23e9c24" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:7.239ex; height:2.843ex;" alt="{\\mathsf  {L}}(A;x)" /></span> be a multivector-valued function of <i>r</i>-grade input <i>A</i> and general position <i>x</i>, linear in its first argument. Then the fundamental theorem of geometric calculus relates the integral of a derivative over the volume <i>V</i> to the integral over its boundary:</p>\n<dl>\n<dd>\n<table cellpadding="5" style="border:2px solid #50C878;background: #ECFCF4; text-align: center;">\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <msub>\n          <mo>&#x222B;<!-- \xe2\x88\xab --></mo>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>V</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mover>\n              <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                <mi mathvariant="sans-serif">L</mi>\n              </mrow>\n              <mo>&#x02D9;<!-- \xcb\x99 --></mo>\n            </mover>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n        <mrow>\n          <mo>(</mo>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n              <mover>\n                <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2207;<!-- \xe2\x88\x87 --></mi>\n                <mo>&#x02D9;<!-- \xcb\x99 --></mo>\n              </mover>\n            </mrow>\n          </mrow>\n          <mi>d</mi>\n          <mi>X</mi>\n          <mo>;</mo>\n          <mi>x</mi>\n          <mo>)</mo>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mo>&#x222E;</mo>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2202;<!-- \xe2\x88\x82 --></mi>\n            <mi>V</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi mathvariant="sans-serif">L</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>d</mi>\n        <mi>S</mi>\n        <mo>;</mo>\n        <mi>x</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle \\int _{V}{\\dot {\\mathsf {L}}}\\left({\\dot {\\nabla }}dX;x\\right)=\\oint _{\\partial V}{\\mathsf {L}}(dS;x)}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/e3f42ade6a342c83d7780ea69d7689ae63e3dfd7" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -2.338ex; width:30.658ex; height:5.843ex;" alt="\\int _{V}{\\dot  {{\\mathsf  {L}}}}\\left({\\dot  {\\nabla }}dX;x\\right)=\\oint _{{\\partial V}}{\\mathsf  {L}}(dS;x)" /></span></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n</dd>\n</dl>\n<p>As an example, let <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi mathvariant="sans-serif">L</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>A</mi>\n        <mo>;</mo>\n        <mi>x</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mo fence="false" stretchy="false">&#x27E8;<!-- \xe2\x9f\xa8 --></mo>\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>x</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mi>A</mi>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>I</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mo fence="false" stretchy="false">&#x27E9;<!-- \xe2\x9f\xa9 --></mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle {\\mathsf {L}}(A;x)=\\langle F(x)AI^{-1}\\rangle }</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/cb166b1b53fc7a145581a7fff320dfc541b73661" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:22.427ex; height:3.176ex;" alt="{\\mathsf  {L}}(A;x)=\\langle F(x)AI^{{-1}}\\rangle " /></span> for a vector-valued function <i>F(x)</i> and a (<i>n</i>-1)-grade multivector <i>A</i>. We find that</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mtable columnalign="right left right left right left right left right left right left" rowspacing="3pt" columnspacing="0em 2em 0em 2em 0em 2em 0em 2em 0em 2em 0em" displaystyle="true">\n            <mtr>\n              <mtd>\n                <msub>\n                  <mo>&#x222B;<!-- \xe2\x88\xab --></mo>\n                  <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                    <mi>V</mi>\n                  </mrow>\n                </msub>\n                <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                  <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                    <mover>\n                      <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                        <mi mathvariant="sans-serif">L</mi>\n                      </mrow>\n                      <mo>&#x02D9;<!-- \xcb\x99 --></mo>\n                    </mover>\n                  </mrow>\n                </mrow>\n                <mrow>\n                  <mo>(</mo>\n                  <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                      <mover>\n                        <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2207;<!-- \xe2\x88\x87 --></mi>\n                        <mo>&#x02D9;<!-- \xcb\x99 --></mo>\n                      </mover>\n                    </mrow>\n                  </mrow>\n                  <mi>d</mi>\n                  <mi>X</mi>\n                  <mo>;</mo>\n                  <mi>x</mi>\n                  <mo>)</mo>\n                </mrow>\n              </mtd>\n              <mtd>\n                <mi></mi>\n                <mo>=</mo>\n                <msub>\n                  <mo>&#x222B;<!-- \xe2\x88\xab --></mo>\n                  <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                    <mi>V</mi>\n                  </mrow>\n                </msub>\n                <mo fence="false" stretchy="false">&#x27E8;<!-- \xe2\x9f\xa8 --></mo>\n                <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                  <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                    <mover>\n                      <mi>F</mi>\n                      <mo>&#x02D9;<!-- \xcb\x99 --></mo>\n                    </mover>\n                  </mrow>\n                </mrow>\n                <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n                <mi>x</mi>\n                <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n                <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                  <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                    <mover>\n                      <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2207;<!-- \xe2\x88\x87 --></mi>\n                      <mo>&#x02D9;<!-- \xcb\x99 --></mo>\n                    </mover>\n                  </mrow>\n                </mrow>\n                <mi>d</mi>\n                <mi>X</mi>\n                <msup>\n                  <mi>I</mi>\n                  <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                    <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n                    <mn>1</mn>\n                  </mrow>\n                </msup>\n                <mo fence="false" stretchy="false">&#x27E9;<!-- \xe2\x9f\xa9 --></mo>\n              </mtd>\n            </mtr>\n            <mtr>\n              <mtd />\n              <mtd>\n                <mi></mi>\n                <mo>=</mo>\n                <msub>\n                  <mo>&#x222B;<!-- \xe2\x88\xab --></mo>\n                  <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                    <mi>V</mi>\n                  </mrow>\n                </msub>\n                <mo fence="false" stretchy="false">&#x27E8;<!-- \xe2\x9f\xa8 --></mo>\n                <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                  <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                    <mover>\n                      <mi>F</mi>\n                      <mo>&#x02D9;<!-- \xcb\x99 --></mo>\n                    </mover>\n                  </mrow>\n                </mrow>\n                <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n                <mi>x</mi>\n                <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n                <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                  <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                    <mover>\n                      <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2207;<!-- \xe2\x88\x87 --></mi>\n                      <mo>&#x02D9;<!-- \xcb\x99 --></mo>\n                    </mover>\n                  </mrow>\n                </mrow>\n                <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                  <mo stretchy="false">|</mo>\n                </mrow>\n                <mi>d</mi>\n                <mi>X</mi>\n                <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                  <mo stretchy="false">|</mo>\n                </mrow>\n                <mo fence="false" stretchy="false">&#x27E9;<!-- \xe2\x9f\xa9 --></mo>\n              </mtd>\n            </mtr>\n            <mtr>\n              <mtd />\n              <mtd>\n                <mi></mi>\n                <mo>=</mo>\n                <msub>\n                  <mo>&#x222B;<!-- \xe2\x88\xab --></mo>\n                  <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                    <mi>V</mi>\n                  </mrow>\n                </msub>\n                <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2207;<!-- \xe2\x88\x87 --></mi>\n                <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x85 --></mo>\n                <mi>F</mi>\n                <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n                <mi>x</mi>\n                <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n                <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                  <mo stretchy="false">|</mo>\n                </mrow>\n                <mi>d</mi>\n                <mi>X</mi>\n                <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                  <mo stretchy="false">|</mo>\n                </mrow>\n                <mo>.</mo>\n              </mtd>\n            </mtr>\n          </mtable>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle {\\begin{aligned}\\int _{V}{\\dot {\\mathsf {L}}}\\left({\\dot {\\nabla }}dX;x\\right)&amp;=\\int _{V}\\langle {\\dot {F}}(x){\\dot {\\nabla }}dXI^{-1}\\rangle \\\\&amp;=\\int _{V}\\langle {\\dot {F}}(x){\\dot {\\nabla }}|dX|\\rangle \\\\&amp;=\\int _{V}\\nabla \\cdot F(x)|dX|.\\end{aligned}}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/eb608d6dd5bf96bc30f20061d80ec6ad191ad867" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -8.132ex; margin-bottom: -0.205ex; width:37.416ex; height:17.843ex;" alt="{\\begin{aligned}\\int _{V}{\\dot  {{\\mathsf  {L}}}}\\left({\\dot  {\\nabla }}dX;x\\right)&amp;=\\int _{V}\\langle {\\dot  {F}}(x){\\dot  {\\nabla }}dXI^{{-1}}\\rangle \\\\&amp;=\\int _{V}\\langle {\\dot  {F}}(x){\\dot  {\\nabla }}|dX|\\rangle \\\\&amp;=\\int _{V}\\nabla \\cdot F(x)|dX|.\\end{aligned}}" /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>and likewise</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mtable columnalign="right left right left right left right left right left right left" rowspacing="3pt" columnspacing="0em 2em 0em 2em 0em 2em 0em 2em 0em 2em 0em" displaystyle="true">\n            <mtr>\n              <mtd>\n                <msub>\n                  <mo>&#x222E;</mo>\n                  <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                    <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2202;<!-- \xe2\x88\x82 --></mi>\n                    <mi>V</mi>\n                  </mrow>\n                </msub>\n                <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                  <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                    <mi mathvariant="sans-serif">L</mi>\n                  </mrow>\n                </mrow>\n                <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n                <mi>d</mi>\n                <mi>S</mi>\n                <mo>;</mo>\n                <mi>x</mi>\n                <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n              </mtd>\n              <mtd>\n                <mi></mi>\n                <mo>=</mo>\n                <msub>\n                  <mo>&#x222E;</mo>\n                  <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                    <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2202;<!-- \xe2\x88\x82 --></mi>\n                    <mi>V</mi>\n                  </mrow>\n                </msub>\n                <mo fence="false" stretchy="false">&#x27E8;<!-- \xe2\x9f\xa8 --></mo>\n                <mi>F</mi>\n                <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n                <mi>x</mi>\n                <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n                <mi>d</mi>\n                <mi>S</mi>\n                <msup>\n                  <mi>I</mi>\n                  <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                    <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n                    <mn>1</mn>\n                  </mrow>\n                </msup>\n                <mo fence="false" stretchy="false">&#x27E9;<!-- \xe2\x9f\xa9 --></mo>\n              </mtd>\n            </mtr>\n            <mtr>\n              <mtd />\n              <mtd>\n                <mi></mi>\n                <mo>=</mo>\n                <msub>\n                  <mo>&#x222E;</mo>\n                  <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                    <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2202;<!-- \xe2\x88\x82 --></mi>\n                    <mi>V</mi>\n                  </mrow>\n                </msub>\n                <mo fence="false" stretchy="false">&#x27E8;<!-- \xe2\x9f\xa8 --></mo>\n                <mi>F</mi>\n                <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n                <mi>x</mi>\n                <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n                <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                  <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                    <mover>\n                      <mi>n</mi>\n                      <mo stretchy="false">&#x005E;<!-- ^ --></mo>\n                    </mover>\n                  </mrow>\n                </mrow>\n                <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                  <mo stretchy="false">|</mo>\n                </mrow>\n                <mi>d</mi>\n                <mi>S</mi>\n                <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                  <mo stretchy="false">|</mo>\n                </mrow>\n                <mo fence="false" stretchy="false">&#x27E9;<!-- \xe2\x9f\xa9 --></mo>\n              </mtd>\n            </mtr>\n            <mtr>\n              <mtd />\n              <mtd>\n                <mi></mi>\n                <mo>=</mo>\n                <msub>\n                  <mo>&#x222E;</mo>\n                  <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                    <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2202;<!-- \xe2\x88\x82 --></mi>\n                    <mi>V</mi>\n                  </mrow>\n                </msub>\n                <mi>F</mi>\n                <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n                <mi>x</mi>\n                <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n                <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x85 --></mo>\n                <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                  <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                    <mover>\n                      <mi>n</mi>\n                      <mo stretchy="false">&#x005E;<!-- ^ --></mo>\n                    </mover>\n                  </mrow>\n                </mrow>\n                <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                  <mo stretchy="false">|</mo>\n                </mrow>\n                <mi>d</mi>\n                <mi>S</mi>\n                <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                  <mo stretchy="false">|</mo>\n                </mrow>\n              </mtd>\n            </mtr>\n          </mtable>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle {\\begin{aligned}\\oint _{\\partial V}{\\mathsf {L}}(dS;x)&amp;=\\oint _{\\partial V}\\langle F(x)dSI^{-1}\\rangle \\\\&amp;=\\oint _{\\partial V}\\langle F(x){\\hat {n}}|dS|\\rangle \\\\&amp;=\\oint _{\\partial V}F(x)\\cdot {\\hat {n}}|dS|\\end{aligned}}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/9547ac891e9b32876080a39343eb8eb9356796ea" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -8.129ex; margin-bottom: -0.209ex; width:33.023ex; height:17.843ex;" alt="{\\begin{aligned}\\oint _{{\\partial V}}{\\mathsf  {L}}(dS;x)&amp;=\\oint _{{\\partial V}}\\langle F(x)dSI^{{-1}}\\rangle \\\\&amp;=\\oint _{{\\partial V}}\\langle F(x){\\hat  {n}}|dS|\\rangle \\\\&amp;=\\oint _{{\\partial V}}F(x)\\cdot {\\hat  {n}}|dS|\\end{aligned}}" /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>Thus we recover the <a href="/wiki/Divergence_theorem" title="Divergence theorem">divergence theorem</a>,</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <msub>\n          <mo>&#x222B;<!-- \xe2\x88\xab --></mo>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>V</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2207;<!-- \xe2\x88\x87 --></mi>\n        <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x85 --></mo>\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>x</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mo stretchy="false">|</mo>\n        </mrow>\n        <mi>d</mi>\n        <mi>X</mi>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mo stretchy="false">|</mo>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mo>&#x222E;</mo>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2202;<!-- \xe2\x88\x82 --></mi>\n            <mi>V</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>x</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x85 --></mo>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mover>\n              <mi>n</mi>\n              <mo stretchy="false">&#x005E;<!-- ^ --></mo>\n            </mover>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mo stretchy="false">|</mo>\n        </mrow>\n        <mi>d</mi>\n        <mi>S</mi>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mo stretchy="false">|</mo>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>.</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle \\int _{V}\\nabla \\cdot F(x)|dX|=\\oint _{\\partial V}F(x)\\cdot {\\hat {n}}|dS|.}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/69ee6f39053a2a18450864d0c4395fe821e26736" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -2.338ex; width:36.248ex; height:5.843ex;" alt="\\int _{V}\\nabla \\cdot F(x)|dX|=\\oint _{{\\partial V}}F(x)\\cdot {\\hat  {n}}|dS|." /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Covariant_derivative">Covariant derivative</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Geometric_calculus&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6" title="Edit section: Covariant derivative">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>A sufficiently smooth <i>k</i>-surface in an <i>n</i>-dimensional space is deemed a <a href="/wiki/Manifold" title="Manifold">manifold</a>. To each point on the manifold, we may attach a <i>k</i>-blade <i>B</i> that is tangent to the manifold. Locally, <i>B</i> acts as a pseudoscalar of the <i>k</i>-dimensional space. This blade defines a <a href="/wiki/Geometric_algebra#Projection_and_rejection" title="Geometric algebra">projection</a> of vectors onto the manifold:</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <msub>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n              <mi class="MJX-tex-caligraphic" mathvariant="script">P</mi>\n            </mrow>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>B</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>A</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>A</mi>\n        <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x85 --></mo>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>B</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mi>B</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle {\\mathcal {P}}_{B}(A)=(A\\cdot B^{-1})B}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/02625ebc55730bd4f1dd77c03f621e1664b1322f" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:20.978ex; height:3.176ex;" alt="{\\mathcal  {P}}_{B}(A)=(A\\cdot B^{{-1}})B" /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>Just as the geometric derivative <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2207;<!-- \xe2\x88\x87 --></mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle \\nabla }</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/a3d0e93b78c50237f9ea83d027e4ebbdaef354b2" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.946ex; height:2.176ex;" alt="\\nabla " /></span> is defined over the entire <i>n</i>-dimensional space, we may wish to define an <i>intrinsic derivative</i> <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2202;<!-- \xe2\x88\x82 --></mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle \\partial }</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/62b4e7c1cedb9564609aefd2aa2309972f455c24" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.329ex; height:2.343ex;" alt="\\partial " /></span>, locally defined on the manifold:</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2202;<!-- \xe2\x88\x82 --></mi>\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n              <mi class="MJX-tex-caligraphic" mathvariant="script">P</mi>\n            </mrow>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>B</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2207;<!-- \xe2\x88\x87 --></mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mi>F</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle \\partial F={\\mathcal {P}}_{B}(\\nabla )F}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/61cd2b57d20f61acd295efbcaa42fd00a59f2e8c" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:14.832ex; height:2.843ex;" alt="\\partial F={\\mathcal  {P}}_{B}(\\nabla )F" /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>(Note: The right hand side of the above may not lie in the tangent space to the manifold. Therefore it is not the same as <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <msub>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n              <mi class="MJX-tex-caligraphic" mathvariant="script">P</mi>\n            </mrow>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>B</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2207;<!-- \xe2\x88\x87 --></mi>\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle {\\mathcal {P}}_{B}(\\nabla F)}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/939b05f730609bcd795d2fa84b23072c35f451e1" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:8.643ex; height:2.843ex;" alt="{\\mathcal  {P}}_{B}(\\nabla F)" /></span>, which necessarily does lie in the tangent space.)</p>\n<p>If <i>a</i> is a vector tangent to the manifold, then indeed both the geometric derivative and intrinsic derivative give the same directional derivative:</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>a</mi>\n        <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x85 --></mo>\n        <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2202;<!-- \xe2\x88\x82 --></mi>\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mi>a</mi>\n        <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x85 --></mo>\n        <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2207;<!-- \xe2\x88\x87 --></mi>\n        <mi>F</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle a\\cdot \\partial F=a\\cdot \\nabla F}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/9508bd7906a02b95f62d2de89cc289421d6ab5ad" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:15.746ex; height:2.343ex;" alt="a\\cdot \\partial F=a\\cdot \\nabla F" /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>Although this operation is perfectly valid, it is not always useful because <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2202;<!-- \xe2\x88\x82 --></mi>\n        <mi>F</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle \\partial F}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/014dfffa1461a32be4e057eee19c864a3b7841c7" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:3.08ex; height:2.343ex;" alt="\\partial F" /></span> itself is not necessarily on the manifold. Therefore we define the <i>covariant derivative</i> to be the forced projection of the intrinsic derivative back onto the manifold:</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>a</mi>\n        <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x85 --></mo>\n        <mi>D</mi>\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n              <mi class="MJX-tex-caligraphic" mathvariant="script">P</mi>\n            </mrow>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>B</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>a</mi>\n        <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x85 --></mo>\n        <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2202;<!-- \xe2\x88\x82 --></mi>\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n              <mi class="MJX-tex-caligraphic" mathvariant="script">P</mi>\n            </mrow>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>B</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>a</mi>\n        <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x85 --></mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n              <mi class="MJX-tex-caligraphic" mathvariant="script">P</mi>\n            </mrow>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>B</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2207;<!-- \xe2\x88\x87 --></mi>\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle a\\cdot DF={\\mathcal {P}}_{B}(a\\cdot \\partial F)={\\mathcal {P}}_{B}(a\\cdot {\\mathcal {P}}_{B}(\\nabla F))}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/9f80f7b20cffcc551439cf4239cfe83b2a724ab5" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:40.307ex; height:2.843ex;" alt="a\\cdot DF={\\mathcal  {P}}_{B}(a\\cdot \\partial F)={\\mathcal  {P}}_{B}(a\\cdot {\\mathcal  {P}}_{B}(\\nabla F))" /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>Since any general multivector can be expressed as a sum of a projection and a rejection, in this case</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>a</mi>\n        <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x85 --></mo>\n        <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2202;<!-- \xe2\x88\x82 --></mi>\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n              <mi class="MJX-tex-caligraphic" mathvariant="script">P</mi>\n            </mrow>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>B</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>a</mi>\n        <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x85 --></mo>\n        <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2202;<!-- \xe2\x88\x82 --></mi>\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mo>+</mo>\n        <msubsup>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n              <mi class="MJX-tex-caligraphic" mathvariant="script">P</mi>\n            </mrow>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>B</mi>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo>&#x22A5;<!-- \xe2\x8a\xa5 --></mo>\n          </mrow>\n        </msubsup>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>a</mi>\n        <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x85 --></mo>\n        <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2202;<!-- \xe2\x88\x82 --></mi>\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mo>,</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle a\\cdot \\partial F={\\mathcal {P}}_{B}(a\\cdot \\partial F)+{\\mathcal {P}}_{B}^{\\perp }(a\\cdot \\partial F),}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/6729aac0a8f827779874c71b77f8978a99e4b2ac" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:34.679ex; height:3.176ex;" alt="a\\cdot \\partial F={\\mathcal  {P}}_{B}(a\\cdot \\partial F)+{\\mathcal  {P}}_{B}^{{\\perp }}(a\\cdot \\partial F)," /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>we introduce a new function, the <a href="/wiki/Shape_tensor" class="mw-redirect" title="Shape tensor">shape tensor</a> <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi mathvariant="sans-serif">S</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>a</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle {\\mathsf {S}}(a)}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/eda42d4f00bffa531be257314f9396930505216d" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:4.373ex; height:2.843ex;" alt="{\\mathsf  {S}}(a)" /></span>, which satisfies</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mo>&#x00D7;<!-- \xc3\x97 --></mo>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi mathvariant="sans-serif">S</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>a</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <msubsup>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n              <mi class="MJX-tex-caligraphic" mathvariant="script">P</mi>\n            </mrow>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>B</mi>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo>&#x22A5;<!-- \xe2\x8a\xa5 --></mo>\n          </mrow>\n        </msubsup>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>a</mi>\n        <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x85 --></mo>\n        <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2202;<!-- \xe2\x88\x82 --></mi>\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mo>,</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle F\\times {\\mathsf {S}}(a)={\\mathcal {P}}_{B}^{\\perp }(a\\cdot \\partial F),}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/8e4ce7c2f2cba9b8e1c8b9d26b710b57fea9fdf4" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:23.84ex; height:3.176ex;" alt="F\\times {\\mathsf  {S}}(a)={\\mathcal  {P}}_{B}^{{\\perp }}(a\\cdot \\partial F)," /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>where <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mo>&#x00D7;<!-- \xc3\x97 --></mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle \\times }</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/0ffafff1ad26cbe49045f19a67ce532116a32703" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.819ex; height:1.676ex;" alt="\\times " /></span> is the commutator product. In a local coordinate basis <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mo fence="false" stretchy="false">{</mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>i</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo fence="false" stretchy="false">}</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle \\{e_{i}\\}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/d45dea23899c892d30b142d73ed0fa19233ee4a5" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:4.247ex; height:2.843ex;" alt="\\{e_{i}\\}" /></span> spanning the tangent surface, the shape tensor is given by</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi mathvariant="sans-serif">S</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>a</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>i</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mo>&#x2227;<!-- \xe2\x88\xa7 --></mo>\n        <msubsup>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n              <mi class="MJX-tex-caligraphic" mathvariant="script">P</mi>\n            </mrow>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>B</mi>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo>&#x22A5;<!-- \xe2\x8a\xa5 --></mo>\n          </mrow>\n        </msubsup>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>a</mi>\n        <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x85 --></mo>\n        <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2202;<!-- \xe2\x88\x82 --></mi>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>i</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mo>.</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle {\\mathsf {S}}(a)=e^{i}\\wedge {\\mathcal {P}}_{B}^{\\perp }(a\\cdot \\partial e_{i}).}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/b2128eed5f5c60f8fe14684acf24dd8540291204" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:23.881ex; height:3.176ex;" alt="{\\mathsf  {S}}(a)=e^{i}\\wedge {\\mathcal  {P}}_{B}^{{\\perp }}(a\\cdot \\partial e_{i})." /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>Importantly, on a general manifold, the covariant derivative does not commute. In particular, the <a href="/wiki/Commutator" title="Commutator">commutator</a> is related to the shape tensor by</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mo stretchy="false">[</mo>\n        <mi>a</mi>\n        <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x85 --></mo>\n        <mi>D</mi>\n        <mo>,</mo>\n        <mspace width="thinmathspace" />\n        <mi>b</mi>\n        <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x85 --></mo>\n        <mi>D</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">]</mo>\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi mathvariant="sans-serif">S</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>a</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mo>&#x00D7;<!-- \xc3\x97 --></mo>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi mathvariant="sans-serif">S</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>b</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mo>&#x00D7;<!-- \xc3\x97 --></mo>\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mo>.</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle [a\\cdot D,\\,b\\cdot D]F=-({\\mathsf {S}}(a)\\times {\\mathsf {S}}(b))\\times F.}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/6c457b5b98d9984ddf7e83417307b47560b27170" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:37.377ex; height:2.843ex;" alt="[a\\cdot D,\\,b\\cdot D]F=-({\\mathsf  {S}}(a)\\times {\\mathsf  {S}}(b))\\times F." /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>Clearly the term <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi mathvariant="sans-serif">S</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>a</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mo>&#x00D7;<!-- \xc3\x97 --></mo>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi mathvariant="sans-serif">S</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>b</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle {\\mathsf {S}}(a)\\times {\\mathsf {S}}(b)}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/eefd4137db13e158bafbe321efb0c9fa4327d0b5" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:11.365ex; height:2.843ex;" alt="{\\mathsf  {S}}(a)\\times {\\mathsf  {S}}(b)" /></span> is of interest. However it, like the intrinsic derivative, is not necessarily on the manifold. Therefore we can define the <a href="/wiki/Riemann_tensor" class="mw-redirect" title="Riemann tensor">Riemann tensor</a> to be the projection back onto the manifold:</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi mathvariant="sans-serif">R</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>a</mi>\n        <mo>&#x2227;<!-- \xe2\x88\xa7 --></mo>\n        <mi>b</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n              <mi class="MJX-tex-caligraphic" mathvariant="script">P</mi>\n            </mrow>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>B</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi mathvariant="sans-serif">S</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>a</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mo>&#x00D7;<!-- \xc3\x97 --></mo>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi mathvariant="sans-serif">S</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>b</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mo>.</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle {\\mathsf {R}}(a\\wedge b)=-{\\mathcal {P}}_{B}({\\mathsf {S}}(a)\\times {\\mathsf {S}}(b)).}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/04c8d16d3e50d6bced71c6eb49618e31b184b530" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:30.079ex; height:2.843ex;" alt="{\\mathsf  {R}}(a\\wedge b)=-{\\mathcal  {P}}_{B}({\\mathsf  {S}}(a)\\times {\\mathsf  {S}}(b))." /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>Lastly, if <i>F</i> is of grade <i>r</i>, then we can define interior and exterior covariant derivatives as</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>D</mi>\n        <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x85 --></mo>\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mo fence="false" stretchy="false">&#x27E8;<!-- \xe2\x9f\xa8 --></mo>\n        <mi>D</mi>\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <msub>\n          <mo fence="false" stretchy="false">&#x27E9;<!-- \xe2\x9f\xa9 --></mo>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>r</mi>\n            <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle D\\cdot F=\\langle DF\\rangle _{r-1}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/4071db56cf85a00b944bf046a52d251a927a4e96" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:17.097ex; height:2.843ex;" alt="D\\cdot F=\\langle DF\\rangle _{{r-1}}" /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>D</mi>\n        <mo>&#x2227;<!-- \xe2\x88\xa7 --></mo>\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mo fence="false" stretchy="false">&#x27E8;<!-- \xe2\x9f\xa8 --></mo>\n        <mi>D</mi>\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <msub>\n          <mo fence="false" stretchy="false">&#x27E9;<!-- \xe2\x9f\xa9 --></mo>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>r</mi>\n            <mo>+</mo>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo>,</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle D\\wedge F=\\langle DF\\rangle _{r+1},}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/a400c34a6f93af681a1f3254c5bd5e1b0524e3fb" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:18.658ex; height:2.843ex;" alt="D\\wedge F=\\langle DF\\rangle _{{r+1}}," /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>and likewise for the intrinsic derivative.</p>\n<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Relation_to_differential_geometry">Relation to differential geometry</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Geometric_calculus&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7" title="Edit section: Relation to differential geometry">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>On a manifold, locally we may assign a tangent surface spanned by a set of basis vectors <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mo fence="false" stretchy="false">{</mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>i</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo fence="false" stretchy="false">}</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle \\{e_{i}\\}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/d45dea23899c892d30b142d73ed0fa19233ee4a5" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:4.247ex; height:2.843ex;" alt="\\{e_{i}\\}" /></span>. We can associate the components of a <a href="/wiki/Metric_tensor" title="Metric tensor">metric tensor</a>, the <a href="/wiki/Christoffel_symbols" title="Christoffel symbols">Christoffel symbols</a>, and the Riemann tensor as follows:</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <msub>\n          <mi>g</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>i</mi>\n            <mi>j</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>i</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x85 --></mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>j</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle g_{ij}=e_{i}\\cdot e_{j}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/d07ebc4a7ecd0e832eff9476527ce4ad373010f9" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -1.005ex; width:11.322ex; height:2.343ex;" alt="g_{{ij}}=e_{i}\\cdot e_{j}" /></span></dd>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <msubsup>\n          <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x0393;<!-- \xce\x93 --></mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>i</mi>\n            <mi>j</mi>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>k</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msubsup>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>i</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x85 --></mo>\n        <mi>D</mi>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>j</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x85 --></mo>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>k</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle \\Gamma _{ij}^{k}=(e_{i}\\cdot De_{j})\\cdot e^{k}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/9279ab5ba0e4284a6090179f72bcdce5f68c25f5" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -1.338ex; width:19.31ex; height:3.676ex;" alt="\\Gamma _{{ij}}^{k}=(e_{i}\\cdot De_{j})\\cdot e^{k}" /></span></dd>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <msub>\n          <mi>R</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>i</mi>\n            <mi>j</mi>\n            <mi>k</mi>\n            <mi>l</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi mathvariant="sans-serif">R</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>i</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo>&#x2227;<!-- \xe2\x88\xa7 --></mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>j</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x85 --></mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>k</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x85 --></mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>l</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle R_{ijkl}=({\\mathsf {R}}(e_{i}\\wedge e_{j})\\cdot e_{k})\\cdot e_{l}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/6a383430b00b168af39472a6a0b05ae3e6a0b897" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -1.005ex; width:26.807ex; height:3.009ex;" alt="R_{{ijkl}}=({\\mathsf  {R}}(e_{i}\\wedge e_{j})\\cdot e_{k})\\cdot e_{l}" /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>These relations embed the theory of differential geometry within geometric calculus.</p>\n<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Relation_to_differential_forms">Relation to differential forms</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Geometric_calculus&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8" title="Edit section: Relation to differential forms">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>In a <a href="/wiki/Local_coordinate_system" class="mw-redirect" title="Local coordinate system">local coordinate system</a> (<i>x</i><sup>1</sup>, ..., <i>x</i><sup><i>n</i></sup>), the coordinate differentials d<i>x</i><sup>1</sup>, ..., d<i>x</i><sup><i>n</i></sup> form a basic set of one-forms within the <a href="/wiki/Coordinate_chart" class="mw-redirect" title="Coordinate chart">coordinate chart</a>. Given a <a href="/wiki/Multi-index" class="mw-redirect" title="Multi-index">multi-index</a> <span class="nowrap"><i>i</i><sub>1</sub>, ..., <i>i</i><sub><i>k</i></sub></span> with <span class="nowrap">1 \xe2\x89\xa4 <i>i<sub>p</sub></i> \xe2\x89\xa4 <i>n</i></span> for <span class="nowrap">1 \xe2\x89\xa4 <i>p</i> \xe2\x89\xa4 <i>k</i></span>, we can define a <i>k</i>-form</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>&#x03C9;<!-- \xcf\x89 --></mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>f</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>I</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mi mathvariant="normal">d</mi>\n        </mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>x</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>I</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>f</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <msub>\n              <mi>i</mi>\n              <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                <mn>1</mn>\n              </mrow>\n            </msub>\n            <mo>,</mo>\n            <msub>\n              <mi>i</mi>\n              <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                <mn>2</mn>\n              </mrow>\n            </msub>\n            <mo>&#x22EF;<!-- \xe2\x8b\xaf --></mo>\n            <msub>\n              <mi>i</mi>\n              <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                <mi>k</mi>\n              </mrow>\n            </msub>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mi mathvariant="normal">d</mi>\n        </mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>x</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <msub>\n              <mi>i</mi>\n              <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                <mn>1</mn>\n              </mrow>\n            </msub>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mo>&#x2227;<!-- \xe2\x88\xa7 --></mo>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mi mathvariant="normal">d</mi>\n        </mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>x</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <msub>\n              <mi>i</mi>\n              <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                <mn>2</mn>\n              </mrow>\n            </msub>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mo>&#x2227;<!-- \xe2\x88\xa7 --></mo>\n        <mo>&#x22EF;<!-- \xe2\x8b\xaf --></mo>\n        <mo>&#x2227;<!-- \xe2\x88\xa7 --></mo>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mi mathvariant="normal">d</mi>\n        </mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>x</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <msub>\n              <mi>i</mi>\n              <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                <mi>k</mi>\n              </mrow>\n            </msub>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mo>.</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle \\omega =f_{I}\\mathrm {d} x^{I}=f_{i_{1},i_{2}\\cdots i_{k}}\\mathrm {d} x^{i_{1}}\\wedge \\mathrm {d} x^{i_{2}}\\wedge \\cdots \\wedge \\mathrm {d} x^{i_{k}}.}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/7b1e286edecdfc2bb5c403b66aab12a5e5460eb8" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -1.005ex; width:45.709ex; height:3.343ex;" alt="\\omega =f_{I}{\\mathrm  {d}}x^{I}=f_{{i_{1},i_{2}\\cdots i_{k}}}{\\mathrm  {d}}x^{{i_{1}}}\\wedge {\\mathrm  {d}}x^{{i_{2}}}\\wedge \\cdots \\wedge {\\mathrm  {d}}x^{{i_{k}}}." /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>We can alternatively introduce a <i>k</i>-grade multivector <i>A</i> as</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>A</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>f</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <msub>\n              <mi>i</mi>\n              <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                <mn>1</mn>\n              </mrow>\n            </msub>\n            <mo>,</mo>\n            <msub>\n              <mi>i</mi>\n              <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                <mn>2</mn>\n              </mrow>\n            </msub>\n            <mo>&#x22EF;<!-- \xe2\x8b\xaf --></mo>\n            <msub>\n              <mi>i</mi>\n              <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                <mi>k</mi>\n              </mrow>\n            </msub>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <msub>\n              <mi>i</mi>\n              <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                <mn>1</mn>\n              </mrow>\n            </msub>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mo>&#x2227;<!-- \xe2\x88\xa7 --></mo>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <msub>\n              <mi>i</mi>\n              <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                <mn>2</mn>\n              </mrow>\n            </msub>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mo>&#x2227;<!-- \xe2\x88\xa7 --></mo>\n        <mo>&#x22EF;<!-- \xe2\x8b\xaf --></mo>\n        <mo>&#x2227;<!-- \xe2\x88\xa7 --></mo>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <msub>\n              <mi>i</mi>\n              <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                <mi>k</mi>\n              </mrow>\n            </msub>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle A=f_{i_{1},i_{2}\\cdots i_{k}}e^{i_{1}}\\wedge e^{i_{2}}\\wedge \\cdots \\wedge e^{i_{k}}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/faa1b8a71589735a155da1fedb71f5232b2c8461" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -1.005ex; width:31.664ex; height:3.343ex;" alt="A=f_{{i_{1},i_{2}\\cdots i_{k}}}e^{{i_{1}}}\\wedge e^{{i_{2}}}\\wedge \\cdots \\wedge e^{{i_{k}}}" /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>and a measure</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mtable columnalign="right left right left right left right left right left right left" rowspacing="3pt" columnspacing="0em 2em 0em 2em 0em 2em 0em 2em 0em 2em 0em" displaystyle="true">\n            <mtr>\n              <mtd>\n                <msup>\n                  <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                    <mi mathvariant="normal">d</mi>\n                  </mrow>\n                  <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                    <mi>k</mi>\n                  </mrow>\n                </msup>\n                <mi>X</mi>\n              </mtd>\n              <mtd>\n                <mi></mi>\n                <mo>=</mo>\n                <mrow>\n                  <mo>(</mo>\n                  <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                    <mi mathvariant="normal">d</mi>\n                  </mrow>\n                  <msup>\n                    <mi>x</mi>\n                    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                      <msub>\n                        <mi>i</mi>\n                        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                          <mn>1</mn>\n                        </mrow>\n                      </msub>\n                    </mrow>\n                  </msup>\n                  <msub>\n                    <mi>e</mi>\n                    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                      <msub>\n                        <mi>i</mi>\n                        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                          <mn>1</mn>\n                        </mrow>\n                      </msub>\n                    </mrow>\n                  </msub>\n                  <mo>)</mo>\n                </mrow>\n                <mo>&#x2227;<!-- \xe2\x88\xa7 --></mo>\n                <mrow>\n                  <mo>(</mo>\n                  <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                    <mi mathvariant="normal">d</mi>\n                  </mrow>\n                  <msup>\n                    <mi>x</mi>\n                    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                      <msub>\n                        <mi>i</mi>\n                        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                          <mn>2</mn>\n                        </mrow>\n                      </msub>\n                    </mrow>\n                  </msup>\n                  <msub>\n                    <mi>e</mi>\n                    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                      <msub>\n                        <mi>i</mi>\n                        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                          <mn>2</mn>\n                        </mrow>\n                      </msub>\n                    </mrow>\n                  </msub>\n                  <mo>)</mo>\n                </mrow>\n                <mo>&#x2227;<!-- \xe2\x88\xa7 --></mo>\n                <mo>&#x22EF;<!-- \xe2\x8b\xaf --></mo>\n                <mo>&#x2227;<!-- \xe2\x88\xa7 --></mo>\n                <mrow>\n                  <mo>(</mo>\n                  <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                    <mi mathvariant="normal">d</mi>\n                  </mrow>\n                  <msup>\n                    <mi>x</mi>\n                    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                      <msub>\n                        <mi>i</mi>\n                        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                          <mi>k</mi>\n                        </mrow>\n                      </msub>\n                    </mrow>\n                  </msup>\n                  <msub>\n                    <mi>e</mi>\n                    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                      <msub>\n                        <mi>i</mi>\n                        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                          <mi>k</mi>\n                        </mrow>\n                      </msub>\n                    </mrow>\n                  </msub>\n                  <mo>)</mo>\n                </mrow>\n              </mtd>\n            </mtr>\n            <mtr>\n              <mtd />\n              <mtd>\n                <mi></mi>\n                <mo>=</mo>\n                <mrow>\n                  <mo>(</mo>\n                  <msub>\n                    <mi>e</mi>\n                    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                      <msub>\n                        <mi>i</mi>\n                        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                          <mn>1</mn>\n                        </mrow>\n                      </msub>\n                    </mrow>\n                  </msub>\n                  <mo>&#x2227;<!-- \xe2\x88\xa7 --></mo>\n                  <msub>\n                    <mi>e</mi>\n                    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                      <msub>\n                        <mi>i</mi>\n                        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                          <mn>2</mn>\n                        </mrow>\n                      </msub>\n                    </mrow>\n                  </msub>\n                  <mo>&#x2227;<!-- \xe2\x88\xa7 --></mo>\n                  <mo>&#x22EF;<!-- \xe2\x8b\xaf --></mo>\n                  <mo>&#x2227;<!-- \xe2\x88\xa7 --></mo>\n                  <msub>\n                    <mi>e</mi>\n                    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                      <msub>\n                        <mi>i</mi>\n                        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                          <mi>k</mi>\n                        </mrow>\n                      </msub>\n                    </mrow>\n                  </msub>\n                  <mo>)</mo>\n                </mrow>\n                <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                  <mi mathvariant="normal">d</mi>\n                </mrow>\n                <msup>\n                  <mi>x</mi>\n                  <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                    <msub>\n                      <mi>i</mi>\n                      <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                        <mn>1</mn>\n                      </mrow>\n                    </msub>\n                  </mrow>\n                </msup>\n                <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                  <mi mathvariant="normal">d</mi>\n                </mrow>\n                <msup>\n                  <mi>x</mi>\n                  <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                    <msub>\n                      <mi>i</mi>\n                      <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                        <mn>2</mn>\n                      </mrow>\n                    </msub>\n                  </mrow>\n                </msup>\n                <mo>&#x22EF;<!-- \xe2\x8b\xaf --></mo>\n                <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                  <mi mathvariant="normal">d</mi>\n                </mrow>\n                <msup>\n                  <mi>x</mi>\n                  <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                    <msub>\n                      <mi>i</mi>\n                      <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                        <mi>k</mi>\n                      </mrow>\n                    </msub>\n                  </mrow>\n                </msup>\n              </mtd>\n            </mtr>\n          </mtable>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>.</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle {\\begin{aligned}\\mathrm {d} ^{k}X&amp;=\\left(\\mathrm {d} x^{i_{1}}e_{i_{1}}\\right)\\wedge \\left(\\mathrm {d} x^{i_{2}}e_{i_{2}}\\right)\\wedge \\cdots \\wedge \\left(\\mathrm {d} x^{i_{k}}e_{i_{k}}\\right)\\\\&amp;=\\left(e_{i_{1}}\\wedge e_{i_{2}}\\wedge \\cdots \\wedge e_{i_{k}}\\right)\\mathrm {d} x^{i_{1}}\\mathrm {d} x^{i_{2}}\\cdots \\mathrm {d} x^{i_{k}}\\end{aligned}}.}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/67d04428bece8af78fb70a87c30ac922c36341a3" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -3.005ex; width:47.007ex; height:7.176ex;" alt="{\\begin{aligned}{\\mathrm  {d}}^{k}X&amp;=\\left({\\mathrm  {d}}x^{{i_{1}}}e_{{i_{1}}}\\right)\\wedge \\left({\\mathrm  {d}}x^{{i_{2}}}e_{{i_{2}}}\\right)\\wedge \\cdots \\wedge \\left({\\mathrm  {d}}x^{{i_{k}}}e_{{i_{k}}}\\right)\\\\&amp;=\\left(e_{{i_{1}}}\\wedge e_{{i_{2}}}\\wedge \\cdots \\wedge e_{{i_{k}}}\\right){\\mathrm  {d}}x^{{i_{1}}}{\\mathrm  {d}}x^{{i_{2}}}\\cdots {\\mathrm  {d}}x^{{i_{k}}}\\end{aligned}}." /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>Apart from a subtle difference in meaning for the exterior product with respect to differential forms versus the exterior product with respect to vectors (indeed one should note that in the former the <i>increments</i> are covectors, whereas in the latter they represent scalars), we see the correspondences of the differential form</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>&#x03C9;<!-- \xcf\x89 --></mi>\n        <mo>&#x2245;<!-- \xe2\x89\x85 --></mo>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>A</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo>&#x2020;<!-- \xe2\x80\xa0 --></mo>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x85 --></mo>\n        <msup>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi mathvariant="normal">d</mi>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>k</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mi>X</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mi>A</mi>\n        <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x85 --></mo>\n        <msup>\n          <mrow>\n            <mo>(</mo>\n            <msup>\n              <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                <mi mathvariant="normal">d</mi>\n              </mrow>\n              <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                <mi>k</mi>\n              </mrow>\n            </msup>\n            <mi>X</mi>\n            <mo>)</mo>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo>&#x2020;<!-- \xe2\x80\xa0 --></mo>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mo>,</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle \\omega \\cong A^{\\dagger }\\cdot \\mathrm {d} ^{k}X=A\\cdot \\left(\\mathrm {d} ^{k}X\\right)^{\\dagger },}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/8499187cd4a1b4446a13885e84ca164c94cdfeb3" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -1.838ex; width:28.732ex; height:5.343ex;" alt="\\omega \\cong A^{{\\dagger }}\\cdot {\\mathrm  {d}}^{k}X=A\\cdot \\left({\\mathrm  {d}}^{k}X\\right)^{{\\dagger }}," /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>its derivative</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mi mathvariant="normal">d</mi>\n        </mrow>\n        <mi>&#x03C9;<!-- \xcf\x89 --></mi>\n        <mo>&#x2245;<!-- \xe2\x89\x85 --></mo>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>D</mi>\n        <mo>&#x2227;<!-- \xe2\x88\xa7 --></mo>\n        <mi>A</mi>\n        <msup>\n          <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo>&#x2020;<!-- \xe2\x80\xa0 --></mo>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x85 --></mo>\n        <msup>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi mathvariant="normal">d</mi>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>k</mi>\n            <mo>+</mo>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mi>X</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>D</mi>\n        <mo>&#x2227;<!-- \xe2\x88\xa7 --></mo>\n        <mi>A</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x85 --></mo>\n        <msup>\n          <mrow>\n            <mo>(</mo>\n            <msup>\n              <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                <mi mathvariant="normal">d</mi>\n              </mrow>\n              <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                <mi>k</mi>\n                <mo>+</mo>\n                <mn>1</mn>\n              </mrow>\n            </msup>\n            <mi>X</mi>\n            <mo>)</mo>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo>&#x2020;<!-- \xe2\x80\xa0 --></mo>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mo>,</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle \\mathrm {d} \\omega \\cong (D\\wedge A)^{\\dagger }\\cdot \\mathrm {d} ^{k+1}X=(D\\wedge A)\\cdot \\left(\\mathrm {d} ^{k+1}X\\right)^{\\dagger },}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/75f5a8befd58c4320e41b161724702311623cc9f" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -1.838ex; width:46.982ex; height:5.343ex;" alt="{\\mathrm  {d}}\\omega \\cong (D\\wedge A)^{{\\dagger }}\\cdot {\\mathrm  {d}}^{{k+1}}X=(D\\wedge A)\\cdot \\left({\\mathrm  {d}}^{{k+1}}X\\right)^{{\\dagger }}," /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>and its <a href="/wiki/Hodge_dual" class="mw-redirect" title="Hodge dual">Hodge dual</a></p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mo>&#x22C6;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x86 --></mo>\n        <mi>&#x03C9;<!-- \xcf\x89 --></mi>\n        <mo>&#x2245;<!-- \xe2\x89\x85 --></mo>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>I</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mi>A</mi>\n        <msup>\n          <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo>&#x2020;<!-- \xe2\x80\xa0 --></mo>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x85 --></mo>\n        <msup>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi mathvariant="normal">d</mi>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>k</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mi>X</mi>\n        <mo>,</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle \\star \\omega \\cong (I^{-1}A)^{\\dagger }\\cdot \\mathrm {d} ^{k}X,}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/adb6ba47c638c768fb3425d907d9ada629583d22" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:20.602ex; height:3.176ex;" alt="\\star \\omega \\cong (I^{{-1}}A)^{{\\dagger }}\\cdot {\\mathrm  {d}}^{k}X," /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>embed the theory of differential forms within geometric calculus.</p>\n<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="History">History</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Geometric_calculus&amp;action=edit&amp;section=9" title="Edit section: History">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Following is a diagram summarizing the history of geometric calculus.</p>\n<div class="center">\n<div class="thumb tnone">\n<div class="thumbinner" style="width:302px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Geometric_Calculus_Family_Tree.png" class="image"><img alt="" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/9a/Geometric_Calculus_Family_Tree.png/300px-Geometric_Calculus_Family_Tree.png" width="300" height="400" class="thumbimage" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/9a/Geometric_Calculus_Family_Tree.png/450px-Geometric_Calculus_Family_Tree.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/9a/Geometric_Calculus_Family_Tree.png/600px-Geometric_Calculus_Family_Tree.png 2x" data-file-width="720" data-file-height="960" /></a>\n<div class="thumbcaption">\n<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Geometric_Calculus_Family_Tree.png" class="internal" title="Enlarge"></a></div>\nHistory of geometric calculus.</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div style="clear:both;"></div>\n<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="References_and_further_reading">References and further reading</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Geometric_calculus&amp;action=edit&amp;section=10" title="Edit section: References and further reading">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class="reflist" style="list-style-type: decimal;">\n<div class="mw-references-wrap">\n<ol class="references">\n<li id="cite_note-1"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-1">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a href="/wiki/David_Hestenes" title="David Hestenes">David Hestenes</a>, Garrett Sobczyk: Clifford Algebra to Geometric Calculus, a Unified Language for mathematics and Physics (Dordrecht/Boston:G.Reidel Publ.Co., 1984, <a href="/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number" title="International Standard Book Number">ISBN</a> <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/90-277-2561-6" title="Special:BookSources/90-277-2561-6">90-277-2561-6</a></span></li>\n</ol>\n</div>\n</div>\n<ul>\n<li><cite class="citation book">Macdonald, Alan (2012). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://faculty.luther.edu/~macdonal/vagc/"><i>Vector and Geometric Calculus</i></a>. Charleston: CreateSpace. <a href="/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number" title="International Standard Book Number">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/9781480132450" title="Special:BookSources/9781480132450">9781480132450</a>. <a href="/wiki/OCLC" title="OCLC">OCLC</a>&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="//www.worldcat.org/oclc/829395829">829395829</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AGeometric+calculu